>Create speaker group<\/strong>.<\/li>\n<li>Select the Google Home Minis you want to sync.<\/li>\n<li>Give your group a name (e.g., \u201cWhole Home\u201d).<\/li>\n<li>Tap <strong>Save<\/strong>.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>Now when you say, \u201cHey Google, play music on Whole Home,\u201d all selected devices will play in sync.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Creating a Stereo Pair<\/h2>\n<p>To pair two identical Google Home Mini speakers into a stereo setup:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open the Google Home app and select one of the devices.<\/li>\n<li>Tap the <strong>Settings<\/strong> gear, then choose <strong>Audio<\/strong>.<\/li>\n<li>Select <strong>Stereo pair<\/strong> and follow the instructions.<\/li>\n<li>Choose which speaker is left and which is right.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>This setup is ideal for creating balanced sound in one room.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Broadcasting Messages<\/h2>\n<p>Use your synced Google Home Minis to send voice messages around your home. Just say:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\u201cHey Google, broadcast \u2018Dinner is ready!\u2019\u201d<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>This feature works across all connected speakers in the same home network.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Adjusting Volume on Synced Devices<\/h2>\n<p>When synced in a group or stereo pair, volume can be adjusted together or individually using:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>The Google Home app<\/li>\n<li>Voice commands (e.g., \u201cHey Google, set volume to 50%\u201d)<\/li>\n<li>Physical buttons on each speaker<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>\u00a0Wikipedia Insight<\/h2>\n<p>Want to learn more about how smart speakers manage synchronized audio? Visit <a href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Multi-room_audio\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Multi-Room Audio on Wikipedia<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Conclusion<\/h2>\n<p>Syncing your Google Home Mini speakers is a great way to enjoy seamless audio across rooms or stereo sound in one space. Whether you\u2019re hosting guests or just love music, synchronized speakers elevate the experience.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>","